et, that is closer to crowd mechanics than edge.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Treat repeated identical PM copy clusters as **anti-signal / ignore-signal** behavior, not followable directional intelligence.\n- This strengthens the case for using PM copy flow only as a crowding-risk overlay, while keeping HL leaderboard state as the better macro directional prior.\n\n**Next:** Add a lightweight cluster metric to the copy pipeline, for example: dominant-title share, dominant `(side, outcome, price)` share, and repeated-wallet concentration. Then test whether high-cluster regimes correlate with worse PM signal quality and should suppress bot confidence.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 22:30 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Copy-Crowding Divergence Confirmed by Post-Session Tape\n\n**Task:** Re-test the copy-crowding divergence idea against the fully post-session market to see whether it holds beyond a single noisy snapshot.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat after active hours, with no missed execution.\n- The post-session tape is pure midpoint ch",
